title: Frank Lloyd Wright Imperial Hotel Peacock Rug Puzzle
description:
Act like an architect and piece together a Frank Lloyd Wright® (American, 1867–1959) favorite. Sort through 500 gold foil-stamped puzzle pieces to engineer a peacock motif rug designed by Wright for the Imperial Hotel in Tokyo in (1913-1922). Made with 90% recycled paper and printed with non-toxic ink.

8 x 8 x 2 in.
